flowRoot.flowPara: Dedicated lanes for bus rapid transit to densify travel in and out of Kenya's urban areas. The plan does not prioritize the power source of the buses, most likely to be diesel.
A modification of the BRT Alternative, however, electric buses are chosen specifically for the BRT service (differentiating it from the main bus service and matatus)

Pollutants from gasoline and diesel vehicles in the city centers contribute to a large portion of the high concentrations of PM 2.5 and NOx. A phase out would see no vehicles allowed in the city centers other than zero tailpipe emission vehicles.

Congestion charging levies a tax on vehicles reduce the number of vehicles entering the city center to reduce congestion and improve local air quality. Levies can be altered for the emissions performance of a given vehicle to eventually remove the dirtiest emitters.
Dedicated intra-city rail line to densify travel in and out of Kenya's urban areas. These nodes would also link up with heavy rail taking passengers between Kenya's cities.
A substantial approach to construct separated lane bike corridors to increase the perceived safety of riding, while initiating bikeshare as another intra-city transit mode for Kenyans.
